    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2119" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δαΐζω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δαίω</span> 2), fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δαΐξω</span>,
          pass. perf. part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δεδαϊγμένος</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">cleave, cut asunder;</span> of carving, <i><span class="en">Od. 14.434</span></i>, but usually of wounding,
          hence <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">cut down, slay</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            21.147</span></i>; pass. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δεδαϊγμένον ὀξέι
            χαλκῷ</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.236</span></i>, etc.;
          metaph., two expressions are to be distinguished, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐδαΐζετο θῡμός</span>, ‘rent’ with cares, sorrows,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 9.9</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            13.320</span></i>, and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὥρμαινε δαϊζόμενος κατὰ
            θῡμὸν</span> | <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">διχθάδια</span>, a
          ‘divided’ mind, <i><span class="en">Il. 14.20</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
